Gibson girl
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a small radio transmitter-receiver.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: A portable radio shaped to be held betwen the knees in an inflatable multi-person rescue dinghy, thought to resemble the upper torso of a corsetted or bodiced Gibson Girl. Poss. infl. in choice of name by `Mae West' for the life jacket. Not used in the Pacific to his knowledge, but in Europe by bomber squadrons and coastal command. Thus not NZ. nf dicts. (?WW2)
